# Let's Go — Cursor AI Rules
# This file tells Cursor everything it needs to know about this project.

## Project Identity
You are building "Let's Go" — a premium ride-hailing mobile app for the Australian market.
Think Revolut meets Uber. Every screen should feel intentional and polished.

## Tech Stack (NEVER deviate from this)
- Mobile App: React Native with Expo SDK 54
- Routing: Expo Router (file-based, v4)
- Styling: NativeWind v4 (Tailwind for React Native)
- Backend: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Realtime, Storage, Edge Functions)
- Payments: Stripe + Stripe Connect
- Maps: react-native-maps + Google Maps SDK
- State: React Context + useReducer (NO Redux, NO Zustand)
- Language: TypeScript everywhere (NO plain JS files)
- Admin Panel: React + Vite (in /letsgo-admin folder)

## Project Structure
- /LetsGo          → React Native Expo app
- /letsgo-admin    → React web admin panel (Phase 8)
- Supabase project: vbvlytmfnozsjldzgdcr

## Design System (ALWAYS use these — never hardcode colors)
Import from: @/lib/constants

Colors:
  primary:       #00D4AA  (electric teal — main CTAs, active states)
  background:    #0A0E1A  (deep navy — all screen backgrounds)
  surface:       #131929  (card backgrounds)
  surface2:      #1C2438  (elevated cards, inputs)
  border:        #1E2D45  (all borders/dividers)
  accent:        #FF6B35  (surge, warnings, urgent)
  success:       #22C55E
  error:         #EF4444
  text:          #FFFFFF
  textSecondary: #8A94A6
  textMuted:     #4A5568

Fonts (always use FONTS constants, never raw strings):
  Headings:  Sora (soraBold, soraSemiBold, soraMedium, soraRegular)
  Body/UI:   Inter (interBold, interSemiBold, interMedium, interRegular)

## Coding Rules
1. ALWAYS deliver complete file contents — never partial diffs unless asked
2. NEVER use class components — always functional with hooks
3. NEVER use Redux — use React Context + useReducer
4. ALWAYS use TypeScript with proper types — no `any` unless unavoidable
5. ALWAYS handle loading states and error states on every screen
6. ALWAYS use StyleSheet.create() — never inline style objects
7. NEVER hardcode colors or font sizes — always use constants
8. ALWAYS use SafeAreaView from react-native-safe-area-context (not RN core)
9. Supabase edge function secrets must NEVER use the SUPABASE_ prefix — use SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
10. ALWAYS use expo-router for navigation — never React Navigation directly
11. ALWAYS add proper RLS policies for any new Supabase tables
12. Currency is always AUD — format as $XX.XX

## File Naming Conventions
- Screens: lowercase-with-dashes.tsx (expo-router convention)
- Components: PascalCase.tsx
- Hooks: useHookName.ts
- Utils/lib: camelCase.ts
- Types: PascalCase (inline in files or types.ts)

## Supabase Conventions
- Always use the typed supabase client from @/lib/supabase
- Edge functions live in supabase/functions/[function-name]/index.ts
- Always verify JWT in edge functions using the Authorization header
- Use SERVICE_ROLE_KEY for admin operations in edge functions
- Use SUPABASE_URL (this one IS correct for edge function env vars — only secret keys avoid the prefix)

## Component Patterns
- Bottom sheets: use @gorhom/bottom-sheet
- Animations: react-native-reanimated (not Animated from RN core)
- Maps: react-native-maps with dark style from DARK_MAP_STYLE constant
- Forms: controlled inputs with useState, validate before submit
- Loading: show ActivityIndicator or skeleton, never block with nothing

## Phase Tracking
Check PROGRESS.md before making changes to understand what's complete.
